<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-13049] Log recovery threads use default thread pool naming</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-13049</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The threads used for log recovery use a pool &lt;tt&gt;Executors.newFixedThreadPool(int)&lt;/tt&gt; and hence pick up the naming scheme from &lt;tt&gt;Executors.defaultThreadFactory()&lt;/tt&gt;. It&apos;s not so clear in a thread dump taken during log recovery what those threads are. They should have clearer names. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
